@startuml
title Data types and MIP propagation flow
autonumber

participant "xforms:bind\n(model definition)" as BIND
participant "xforms-rebuild\n(src/saxon-xforms.xsl)" as REBUILD
participant "add-context mode\n(src/saxon-xforms.xsl)" as ADDCTX
participant "xforms-recalculate\n(src/saxon-xforms.xsl)" as RECALC
participant "recalculate-binding\n(src/saxon-xforms.xsl)" as RECALC_BIND
participant "xforms-revalidate\n(src/saxon-xforms.xsl)" as REVAL
participant "xsd-helpers.xsl\nxsdh:is-type-valid\nxsdh:canonical-type" as XSD
collections "validationMIPs JS registry\n(instanceId|ref -> valid,required)" as VMIP
participant "DOM Controls" as DOM

== Rebuild Phase ==
BIND -> REBUILD : binds parsed from model
REBUILD -> ADDCTX : add-context mode\nresolve @nodeset to instance nodes
ADDCTX -> ADDCTX : annotate bind with\n@instance-context\n@nodeset (absolute)

== Recalculate Phase ==
RECALC -> RECALC_BIND : for each bind
RECALC_BIND -> RECALC_BIND : evaluate @calculate\n(try/catch for type coercion)
RECALC_BIND -> RECALC_BIND : evaluate @relevant\n(boolean coercion)
RECALC_BIND -> RECALC_BIND : evaluate @readonly\n(boolean, inherits from parent)
RECALC_BIND -> RECALC_BIND : evaluate @required\n(boolean)
RECALC_BIND -> RECALC_BIND : evaluate @constraint\n(boolean expression)

== Revalidate Phase ==
REVAL -> REVAL : check-required-fields\nfor each required=true() binding
REVAL -> REVAL : check-constraints-on-fields\nevaluate constraint expressions
REVAL -> REVAL : check-required-bindings\nvalidate non-empty + required
REVAL -> REVAL : check-instance-xsi-types\nvalidate xsi:type attributes
REVAL -> XSD : xsdh:canonical-type()\nnormalize type QNames
REVAL -> XSD : xsdh:is-type-valid()\nvalidate value against XSD type
REVAL -> VMIP : clearValidationMIPs()\nstart new cycle
REVAL -> VMIP : setValidationMIP(instanceId, ref,\nvalid, required)

== Refresh Phase (MIP Projection to DOM) ==
VMIP --> REVAL : getValidationMIPValid/Required
REVAL --> DOM : refreshOutputs-JS\nupdate output values + project\nxforms-valid/invalid +\nxforms-required/optional
REVAL --> DOM : refreshRelevantFields-JS\nshow/hide based on relevant
REVAL --> DOM : getRelevantStatus\ngetHtmlClass\napply readonly/required CSS classes
REVAL --> DOM : apply class to control and wrapper\nfor input/select/textarea
REVAL --> DOM : dispatch xforms-valid\nor xforms-invalid events
@enduml
